Instead of saying: 

        winCount = winCount + 1;
you can say: 

        winCount++; //Which means the same thing, but looks professional 

**If you define them inside a loop, they will only be available inside that loop block, and will be reset every time the loop repeats.**

 **As for why your game doesn&#39;t register a win, the break keyword only
   breaks the inner most loop. This leaves you inside the first while
   loop.**

Also, there is no reason to assign letter to &#39;0&#39;.
